    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-23T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-23T12:00:00-05:00" n="172"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d172">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710 Consultation (3)/100: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">White</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-23T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 23, 1941—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>276. The Dominican Government has approached the Haitian Government for support
                    to a resolution to be proposed at Rio de Janeiro to the effect that those
                    American Governments which have not yet declared war should do so cojointly.</p>
                <pb facs="0142" n="132" xml:id="pg_132"/>
                <p>The Haitian Minister for Foreign Affairs would be grateful for the Department’s
                    reactions as soon as possible. He himself has no objections to supporting such a
                    resolution.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
